 United Kingdom":"Thorley, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom","Thorley, Hertfordshire, England":"Thorley, Hertfordshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Joan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Contracted form of Old French <i>Jo(h)anne</i>, from Latin <i>Io(h)anna</i> (  see  Joanna  ). In England this was the usual feminine form of   John   from the Middle English period onwards and was extremely popular, but in the 16th and 17th centuries it steadily lost ground to   Jane .  It was strongly revived in the first part of the 20th century, partly under the influence of  George Bernard Shaw's  play St Joan (  1923 ), based on the life of  Joan of Arc  (  1412–31 ). Claiming to be guided by the voices of the saints, she persuaded the French dauphin to defy the occupying English forces and have himself crowned, and she led the French army that raised the siege of Orleans in  1429 . The following year she was captured by the Burgundians and sold to the English, and a year later she was burned at the stake for witchcraft at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":14,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Joan Babelake was born before 1368, in Thorley, Hertfordshire, England, her father, John Babelake, was 27 and her mother, Joan, was 26. She had at least 1 son with John Wylley. She died after 1406, in her hometown."},"et":{"before 1368–after 1406":"enne 1368–pärast 1406","1368–1406":"1368–1406","–Female":"Surnud","1360–1409":"1360–1409","1390–1462":"1390–1462","1340–Male":"1340–Surnud","1342–Female":"1342–Surnud","about 1390":"umbes 1390","before 1368":"enne 1368","1368":"1368","after 1406":"pärast 1406","1342":"1342","1462":"1462","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1409":"1409","1360":"1360","1390":"1390","1406":"1406","Thorley, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Thorley, Hertfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Thorley, Hertfordshire, England":"Thorley, Hertfordshire, England"},"fi":{"before 1368–after 1406":"ennen vuotta 1368–1406 jälkeen","1368–1406":"1368–1406","–Female":"Kuollut","1360–1409":"1360–1409","1390–1462":"1390–1462","1340–Male":"1340–Kuollut","1342–Female":"1342–Kuollut","about 1390":"noin 1390","before 1368":"ennen vuotta 1368","1368":"1368","after 1406":"1406 jälkeen","1342":"1342","1462":"1462","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1409":"1409","1360":"1360","1390":"1390","1406":"1406","Thorley, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Thorley, Hertfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Thorley, Hertfordshire, England":"Thorley, Hertfordshire, England"},"fr":{"before 1368–after 1406":"avant 1368–après 1406","1368–1406":"1368–1406","–Female":"Décédée","1360–1409":"1360–1409","1390–1462":"1390–1462","1340–Male":"1340–Décédé","1342–Female":"1342–Décédée","about 1390":"environ 1390","before 1368":"avant 1368","1368":"1368","after 1406":"après 1406","1342":"1342","1462":"1